Project Purpose

The purpose of this project is to design and develop a Blood Bank Management System that automates donor management, blood inventory tracking, and blood request processing. The system aims to reduce manual errors, improve response time during emergencies, and ensure efficient utilization of blood resources.

Project Objectives

To develop a centralized system for managing blood bank operations

To maintain accurate and real-time blood inventory records

To streamline blood donor registration and management

To enable quick processing of blood requests during emergencies

To reduce blood wastage due to poor tracking and expiration

Project Scope

In-Scope:

Donor registration and management

Blood inventory tracking

Blood request and allocation

User authentication and role-based access

Reporting and notifications

Out-of-Scope:

Mobile application development

Online payment processing

Integration with national blood bank systems

Logistics and transportation tracking

