| Project Guide / Faculty   | Review and evaluation                    |
| Development Team          | Design, development, and testing         |
Assumptions

Users have access to the internet and a web browser

Data entered into the system is accurate

Project will be completed within the academic schedule

Constraints

Limited development time

Academic project resources only

Web-based implementation

Risks

Incomplete or incorrect data entry

Limited user adoption due to lack of training

Time constraints affecting feature completeness

Success Criteria

The project will be considered successful if:

All functional and non-functional requirements are met

The system runs without major defects

Core features operate as expected

Documentation is complete and accurate

Approval

This Project Charter formally authorizes the Blood Bank Management System project and provides high-level direction for planning, execution, and evaluation.
